Introduction

JBJ (Korean: 제이비제이; Japanese: ジェイビージェイ), short for Just Be Joyful, was a six-member project boy group formed by LOEN Entertainment. The group consisted of fan-favorite contestants from Produce 101 season 2 who did not get to reach Top 11. The group made their official debut on October 18, 2017 with the mini album Fantasy. Following the end of the group's seven-month contract, they eventually disbanded on April 30, 2018.
